      "side": 1,
      "message": "Changed this to non-pointer. However I do have an opinion that it should be SecurityOptions instead of boolean flag because:\n1) Makes future plumbing easier for new features like attestation since they go into the SecurityOptions container.\n2) There is no need for this particular part of scheduler to look one level down into the options container while at the other place where I explicitly use a \"UseProjectScopedServiceAccount\" is intentionally exposes semantics information because the engine logic deals with it explicitly.\n\nWDYT?",
