      "writtenOn": "2019-01-18T17:16:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "why? and why 1000? do you intend to eventually get rid of security_options?\n\nFrom my PoV, our goal should removing opportunity to have UseProjectScopedServiceAccount\u003dFalse. This means first allowing opt-in, then ensuring everybody opted in, then removing this flag entirely.\n\nSometimes it\u0027s easier to do this if flag had 3 values: \n  * default (whatever is default on server)\n  * YES aka Opt In\n  * NO aka Opt out.\nthen server default starts with NO. Eventually, it becomes YES, thus if some client decides to revert, client has to do so explicitly by saying \"NO\".\n\nGiven that set of projects using scheduler is still rather small, it\u0027s probably fine to go with boolean.",
      "revId": "6208bd1bb7d58014f3c365ec98e4ee8333bbf0cb",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
